query.description:
Retrieve only data matching the defined search value.
Simple search can be done like the following example: ``` search={"host.name":"Central"} ```
Complex search can be done with aggregators and operators.
Available search aggregators are:
  * `$or`
  * `$and`

Available search operators are:
  * `$eq`  equal
  * `$neq`  not equal
  * `$lt`  less than
  * `$le`  less or equal than
  * `$gt`  greater than
  * `$ge`  greater or equal than
  * `$lk`  like
  * `$nk`  not like
  * `$in`  in
  * `$ni`  not in

Examples without nested aggregators:
  ```
  search={
    "$or":[
      {"host.name":{"$eq":"name_1"}},
      {"host.name":{"$eq":"name_2"}}
    ]
  }
  ```
  ```
  search={
    "$and":[
      {"host.address":{"$rg":"^10\.0\.0\.\d+$"}},
      {"host.name":{"$lk":"fr%"}}
    ]
  }
  ```

Example with nested aggregators:
  ```
  search={
    "$or":[
      {
        "$and":[
          {"host.address":{"$rg":"^10\.0\.0\.\d+$"}},
          {"host.name":{"$lk":"fr%"}}
        ]
      },
      {
        "$and":[
          {"host.address":{"$rg":"^192\.168\.0\.\d+$"}},
          {"host.name":{"$lk":"us%"}}
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

